<div class="text-center">
    <p>
        This application provides a comprehensive overview of Language-Integrated Query (LINQ) in C#,
        demonstrating its capabilities for standardized data querying and manipulation across various
        data sources. The application introduces extension methods, which allow developers to add
        functionality to existing types without modifying the original code, and lambda expressions,
        which are anonymous functions used for creating concise, passable code blocks. The majority
        of the code focuses on LINQ's practical implementation through numerous operators and syntax
        options, comparing extension method syntax with query syntax across various scenarios
        including filtering, sorting, joining, grouping, and aggregating data. Throughout the
        application, code examples demonstrate a three-tier data model of Suppliers, Parts, and
        SupplierParts, showing how to perform common database operations using LINQ's declarative
        approach within the application, with corresponding views to display the results.
    </p>
